nfrastructure and is load-bearing.\\n- `src/utils.ts` is widely imported; keep edits small and covered by tests.\\n\\n## Coding Conventions\\n\\n- TypeScript, ESM.\\n- Match existing style: 2-space indent, double quotes, semicolons.\\n- Prefer explicit types at public boundaries.\\n- Keep changes scoped; do not refactor large build paths opportunistically.\\n\\n## Testing Guidance\\n\\n- Add or update tests for behavior changes.\\n- Avoid tests that only execute setup. Assert observable output, emitted files,\\n  errors, or CLI results.\\n\\n## Agent Safety Rules\\n\\n- Do not publish packages.\\n- Do not run `npm publish`, `pnpm publish`, `git push`, or create tags unless\\n  explicitly requested.\\n- Treat `src/index.ts`, `src/esbuild/index.ts`, `src/plugin.ts`, and\\n  `src/utils.ts` as load-bearing. Read callers/importers before changing them.\\n- Prefer additive, narrowly scoped edits over broad rewrites.\\n```\\n\\nThat gives agents the minimum useful contract: how to set up, how to verify, where responsibilities live, and what operations are unsafe.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"turn.completed\",\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":42264,\"cached_input_tokens\":12160,\"output_tokens\":639,\"reasoning_output_tokens\":29}}\n",
