sion behavior are all mixed into one implicit shape.\\n\\n**`return_shape_roulette`**\\n\\nAffected findings:\\n`crime_00051`, `crime_00052`, `crime_00055` in `src/esbuild/svelte.ts`.\\n\\nRefactor plan:\\n- Add explicit return types from esbuild:\\n  - plugin factory returns `Plugin`\\n  - resolve handler returns `OnResolveResult | null | undefined`\\n  - load handler returns `OnLoadResult | null | undefined`\\n- Extract object construction into named helpers:\\n  - `resolveSveltePath(...)`\\n  - `createSvelteLoadResult(...)`\\n  - `toEsbuildWarnings(...)`\\n  - `toEsbuildError(...)`\\n- Use named intermediate result types if esbuild’s native types are too broad.\\n\\nWhat an agent could get wrong today:\\nThe same closure returns incompatible object literals like `{ args, namespace, path }`, `{ location, text }`, and `{ code }`. Without explicit return types, an agent may copy the wrong object shape between esbuild hooks, return warning/error objects where load results are expected, or accidentally rely on TypeScript inference that accepts a broad union but violates esbuild’s runtime contract.\\n\\n**Suggested Order**\\n\\n1. Add explicit internal types first, with no behavior change.\\n2. Extract pure helpers from `src/rollup.ts` and `src/esbuild/svelte.ts`.\\n3. Rename internal effectful helpers while preserving public exports.\\n4. Split `src/index.ts` orchestration last, because it is load-bearing and has the largest blast radius.\\n5. Add focused tests around Rollup cleanup/config generation and Svelte resolve/load behavior before moving code.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"turn.completed\",\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":39772,\"cached_input_tokens\":12160,\"output_tokens\":1255,\"reasoning_output_tokens\":53}}\n",
