lte, swc, …)\n- `src/rollup.ts`        — rollup config builder for .d.ts\n- `src/api-extractor.ts` — Microsoft API Extractor integration\n- `src/plugin.ts`        — internal plugin contract (fan-in 10)\n- `src/utils.ts`         — shared helpers (fan-in 18, load-bearing)\n- `test/utils.ts`        — test harness used by every spec\n\n## Load-bearing files (read before editing)\n- `src/utils.ts`         — 18 importers\n- `src/plugin.ts`        — 10 importers, defines plugin lifecycle\n- `src/log.ts`           — 9 importers\n- `test/utils.ts`        — 9 importers (test contract)\n\n## Conventions\n- Plugins return esbuild/rollup-shaped objects; don't widen those return types.\n- `removeFiles`, `setSilent`, and `createLogger` have side effects despite\n  innocuous names — keep them in orchestrator code, not pure helpers.\n- Long functions in `src/index.ts`, `src/esbuild/index.ts`, and\n  `src/rollup.ts` are tolerated; prefer additive edits over splitting.\n\n## Don't\n- Don't introduce new sync I/O (`*Sync`) in domain code; async exists.\n- Don't add `Date.now()` / `new Date()` outside logging — bundle timings\n  are the only sanctioned use.\n- Don't restructure `src/utils.ts` or `src/plugin.ts` without checking\n  importers first.\n\n## Release\nChangesets-driven. See `CONTRIBUTING.md` for the release flow.\n```\n\nThat clears `crime_00009`: any one of `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, or a `SKILL.md` satisfies the detector. AGENTS.md is the most portable across coding agents.",
