/Users/andrew/dev/crimes-release-a/evals/results/0.7.4/claude/context-04-monorepo.json:7:  "response": "## Agent context: missing\n\n`crimes scan` confirms it — finding **`crime_00011` (Missing Agent Context, medium / confidence 0.9)**:\n\n- no `AGENTS.md` at repo root\n- no `CLAUDE.md` at repo root\n- no `.claude/skills/*/SKILL.md`\n- `package.json` declares bins (`tsup`, `tsup-node`) that agents have no documented way to discover\n\n## Consequence for future agent work\n\nAn agent landing here cold has to infer everything from the file tree:\n\n- **Which commands run tests/build/lint?** Not discoverable without reading `package.json` scripts and guessing.\n- **What's load-bearing?** The scan flags `src/plugin.ts` (fan-in 10), `src/utils.ts` (fan-in 18), `src/log.ts` (fan-in 9), and `src/esbuild/index.ts` / `src/index.ts` (huge fan-out) — touch these wrong and the ripple is wide. An agent won't know to read importers first.\n- **Where do the God Functions live?** `main` (cli-main), `runEsbuild`, `build`, `getRollupConfig` — all 100–300 lines. An agent editing one section of `build` (293 LOC) is likely to miss interactions in another section it never loaded.\n- **Convention traps:** `build`, `buildAll`, `buildStart`, `getRollupConfig` have safe-sounding names but do I/O (False Identity findings). Without `AGENTS.md` saying \"treat these as side-effectful,\" agents will treat them as pure transforms.\n\nNet: confident-but-wrong edits become the default failure mode.\n\n## Minimal AGENTS.md skeleton (would clear the finding)\n\n```markdown\n# AGENTS.md\n\n## What this is\ntsup — a zero-config TS/JS bundler built on esbuild. Published as `tsup`\nwith bins `tsup` and `tsup-node`.\n\n## Commands\n- Install: `pnpm install`\n- Build:   `pnpm build`\n- Test:    `pnpm test`        (Vitest, integration-heavy — slow)\n- Lint:    `pnpm lint`\n- Typecheck: `pnpm typecheck`\n\n## Layout\n- `src/index.ts`           — public API entry, orchestrates `build()`\n- `src/cli-main.ts`        — CLI argument parsing + dispatch\n- `src/esbuild/`           — esbuild integration + plugin shims\n- `src/rollup.ts`          — rollup-based .d.ts pipeline\n- `src/plugin.ts`          — internal plugin contract (load-bearing)\n- `src/utils.ts`           — shared helpers (load-bearing, 18 importers)\n- `src/log.ts`             — logging (load-bearing, 9 importers)\n- `test/`                  — Vitest integration suites\n\n## Conventions\n- TS strict mode; no `any` in new code.\n- New flags go through `normalizeOptions` in `src/index.ts`.\n- Date.now()/new Date() in domain code is discouraged — there's existing\n  drift, don't add to it.\n\n## Load-bearing files — read importers before editing\n- `src/plugin.ts`, `src/utils.ts`, `src/log.ts`, `src/index.ts`,\n  `src/esbuild/index.ts`.\n\n## Known sharp edges\n- `build()`, `buildAll()`, `getRollupConfig()`, `buildStart()` look pure\n  but perform I/O (file removal, logger mutation). Don't treat as\n  transforms.\n- Several large functions (`main`, `runEsbuild`, `build`, `getRollupConfig`,\n  `postcssPlugin`) mix concerns — when editing, scope changes narrowly\n  and prefer additive edits.\n\n## Before you commit\n- `pnpm test` must pass.\n- Snapshot updates need a reason in the commit message.\n```\n\nThat's enough surface to clear `missing_agent_context` and give the next agent commands, layout, load-bearing pointers, and the False-Identity warnings the scan already surfaced.",
